# Portfolio CSV Format

Use this format for portfolio holdings files (e.g. `portfolio/portfolio.csv`).  
**Directive:** The system uses live data only. Tickers and positions come from CSV (or broker export) at runtime; no hardcoded ticker lists in code.

## Header (exact column order)

| Column        | Type    | Example        | Notes                          |
|---------------|---------|----------------|--------------------------------|
| ticker        | string  | AAPL, VTI      | Stock or ETF symbol            |
| shares        | integer | 50             | Number of shares               |
| avg_cost      | float   | 145.20         | Average cost per share, no $   |
| purchase_date | date    | 2022-03-15     | YYYY-MM-DD                     |
| sector        | string  | Technology     | Sector name                    |
| asset_class   | string  | Equity, ETF    | Equity or ETF                  |
| notes         | string  | Core holding   | Free text                      |

## Conventions

- CSV delimiter: comma. Quote fields that contain commas.
- One header row, then one data row per position.
- No blank rows between data rows.
- Dates always `YYYY-MM-DD`. Numbers without currency symbols.

## Example row

```csv
ticker,shares,avg_cost,purchase_date,sector,asset_class,notes
AAPL,50,145.20,2022-03-15,Technology,Equity,Core holding
```

When reading or writing portfolio CSV in this project, preserve this column order and types.
